  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>The primary objective of this study is to evaluate the long-term effect of growth hormone treatment on the development of diabetes during the treatment period in short children born SGA.</measure>
    <time_frame>Patients discontinues treatment when final height is reached.</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>•to report the incidence of anti-rhGH AB´s and of E. coli host cell peptide AB´s during Omnitrope® treatment •to evaluate the efficacy of Omnitrope® treatment in SGA, IGF-I and IGFBP-3 levels during treatment and incidence and severity of adverse events</measure>
    <time_frame>Patients discontinues treatment when final height is reached.</time_frame>
  </secondary_outcome>
